# API Documentation Standards

- Public API examples must use `https://api.zelf.world`.
- Do not use localhost URLs in public docs.
- For protected endpoints, document the auth flow when needed: create session, extract JWT, then call the protected API.
- Document both success and error responses with real HTTP status codes.
- Prefer Docusaurus `Tabs` and `TabItem` for response variants and multi-language examples.
- Keep language coverage aligned with the current backend standard: cURL, Node.js, Python, PHP, and Rust unless the page is intentionally narrower.
- Treat backend behavior in `zelf` as the source of truth for parameters, auth requirements, and response fields.

## Examples

```md
<!-- Prefer -->
curl -X GET "https://api.zelf.world/api/tags/search?tagName=username.zelf"
```

```md
<!-- Avoid -->
curl -X GET "http://localhost:3003/api/tags/search?tagName=username.zelf"
```
